III. ORIGIN: THE ROOT-HUSK COLONY ("The Dojo")
Timeline: Born 25-30 Years Ago
Location & Purpose
Deep in the toxic heart of Black Marsh, where the air is thick with spore-choke and the water burns mammalian skin, lies the Root-Husk. It is not a school; it is a filtration system designed by the Shadowscales to turn soft flesh into hard instruments of Sithis.
The Intake
Birth: Born in the ColonyΓÇöno mother, only the Hist and the Instructors
The Foreign Legion: Raised in communal mud-pits with 50+ other non-Argonian children (Bosmer, Khajiit, Orcs)
The Challenge: Had to work twice as hard because they weren't born with scales
Philosophy: Not family, but tools being forged together
The Indoctrination
Core Teaching: The world is chaotic noise and pain; the Void (Sithis) is the only silence.
Philosophy of Killing: Not murder, but "quieting the noise." They weren't taught to hate the world; they were taught that it was a mess that needed to be organized through death.
Defining Memory: The Water-Box
To mimic Argonian water-breathing, non-lizard children were held underwater in cages until their lungs spasmed. They learned to:
Slow their heart rates
Consume less oxygen
Exist in a state of suspended animation
Varon's Breakthrough: He learned to stop fearing the drowning. He learned to love the silence under the water. This is when he truly understood the Void.
The Bird Test
When ordered to wring the necks of birds they caught:
Varon: Looked at it as dinner
Saijah: Looked at the creature with recognition (she hesitated)
This is when he knew they would walk different paths.

IV. THE TRANSFORMATION: THE RITUAL OF THE KNIFE
Timeline: 10 Years Ago (Upon Reaching Maturity)
Selection & Purpose
Varon was selected for the Infiltration Cadre. The Shadowscales needed agents who could walk into the High King's court or the Emperor's palace without drawing the suspicion that beast-races attract.
The Logic: "Magic can be detected; flesh is undeniable."
The Procedure
No Anesthesia. The surgery was a rite of passage proving commitment to the Void.
Varon lay awake while Argonian chirurgeons:
Shaved down the sharp points of his jaw
Clipped the tips of his ears
Thickened his brow ridge
Pulled skin tight and stitched
He felt everything.
The Eyes: The Final Step
Bosmer eyes are pools of blackΓÇöinstantly recognizable. To truly pass as Breton, he had to change them. The solution: a daily alchemical tincture that clouds his sclera to murky grey.
"It burns. He likes the burn. It reminds him of his commitment."
The Result
He looks like a Breton. But inside, his bone structure, his musculature, his instincts are pure Bosmer predator.
"He is a wolf wearing a sheep's face, and the mask is stapled on."
Current Pain Status
He is constantly in low-level pain from:
Surgery scars
Eye drops
Nerve damage
He uses this pain to anchor himself. If he is ever relaxed, he taps his finger against the scar behind his ear to remind himself of the knife.

