The Hroki Contract: Since they could not kill Hroki at the camp (now a Captain surrounded by fifty loyal men), Varon has adjusted the plan:
"The Sergeant is now a Captain. He is surrounded by fifty men who would die for him. To strike tonight is suicide. The Brotherhood does not throw away assets on suicide runs. Hroki goes to Windhelm. We will follow. I will travel with you, 'Brother.' I will teach you how to prune a branch that has grown too high."
Purpose: This keeps the assassination plot active while justifying Varon's insertion into the party.
3. Kyboh: "The Kinetic Noise"
The Dynamic: Distant respect.
Varon's View: Understands physical discipline. Recognizes that Kyboh has pushed his body to the limit (the burned arms). Views Kyboh as a fellow weapon, albeit a loud and clumsy one.
Interaction: Professional courtesy between two people who have sacrificed their bodies for their craft.
4. Alfonso: "The Rot"
The Dynamic: Professional curiosity.
Varon's Perspective: The Shadowscales revere Sithis (The Void) and the Cycle of Life/Death. Alfonso's new "Vrykolas" natureΓÇöconsuming and recycling lifeΓÇöis fascinating to Varon. He doesn't like it, but he respects the purity of the function.
Philosophy: Death feeding into new life is fundamentally aligned with the Void's purpose, even if the execution is grotesque.

